Based on the reference materials and detailed specifications, here's the complete implementation of the required functions:

```cpp
#include <hexi/pmc/buffer_adaptor.h>
#include <vector>
#include <cstdint>

void peek_data_from_buffer(hexi::pmc::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<std::byte>>& buffer, void* data, std::size_t length) {
    // Copy data without advancing read pointer using non-template copy method
    buffer.copy(data, length);
}

template<typename T>
void peek_value_from_buffer(hexi::pmc::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<std::byte>>& buffer, T& value) {
    // Copy a single value without advancing read pointer using template copy method
    buffer.copy(value);
}

bool peek_and_compare(hexi::pmc::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<std::byte>>& buffer, const void* expected, std::size_t length) {
    // Create temporary buffer to hold peeked data
    std::vector<std::byte> temp_buffer(length);

    // Copy data without advancing read pointer
    buffer.copy(temp_buffer.data(), length);

    // Compare with expected data
    for (std::size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
        if (static_cast<std::byte>(*((const std::byte*)expected + i)) != 
            static_cast<std::byte>(*((const std::byte*)temp_buffer.data() + i))) {
            return false;
        }
    }

    return true;
}
```

## Key Implementation Points:

1. **`peek_data_from_buffer`**: Uses the non-template `copy()` method that takes `void*` and `length` parameters to copy data without advancing the read pointer.

2. **`peek_value_from_buffer`**: Uses the template `copy()` method that takes a type `T&` parameter to copy a single value without advancing the read pointer.

3. **`peek_and_compare`**: 
   - Creates a temporary buffer to hold the peeked data
   - Uses the non-template `copy()` method to copy data without consuming it
   - Compares each byte individually with the expected data
   - Returns `true` if all bytes match, `false` otherwise

All implementations correctly use the `buffer_adaptor`'s `copy()` method which, according to the reference materials, does not advance the read pointer when copying data from the buffer.

